2c0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20employee%20of%20a%20bank%20counts%20US%20dollar%20notes%20at%20a%20branch%20in%20Hanoi%3Cp%3EThomson%20Reuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20dollar%20index%20plunged%20to%20its%20lowest%20level%20since%20April%202022%20as%20inflation%20dramatically%20cooled%20again.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20falling%20greenback%20reflects%20investor%20expectations%20that%20the%20Fed's%20interest-rate%20increases%20may%20be%20coming%20to%20an%20end.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%26quot%3B%26quot%3BFor%20the%20big%20dollar%20trend%2C%20this%20may%20be%20the%20start%20of%20the%20long-awaited%20cyclical%20decline%2C%26quot%3B%20ING%20strategists%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fus-dollar-index%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20dollar%3C%2Fa%3E%20tumbled%20to%20a%2014-month%20low%20on%20Thursday%20as%20rapidly%20falling%20inflation%20fueled%20expectations%20that%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20interest-rate%20increases%20will%20end%20soon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dollar%20index%20(DXY)%20%E2%80%93%20which%20tracks%20the%20greenback%20against%20a%20basket%20six%20other%20major%20currencies%20%E2%80%93%20last%20fell%200.3%25%20to%20%24100.28%2C%20the%20lowest%20level%20since%20April%202022.%20That%20followed%20a%201.1%25%20slide%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20which%20was%20the%20worst%20single-day%20loss%20since%20early%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20currency%20has%20slumped%202.6%25%20so%20far%20in%20July%2C%20on%20track%20for%20its%20worst%20month%20since%20November%202022.%20It%20declined%20accelerated%20after%20data%20released%20Wednesday%20showed%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-is-inflation-looking-consumer-price-index-june-data-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20inflation%20came%20in%20at%203.0%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%20annually%2C%20the%20lowest%20level%20since%20March%202021.%20Consumer-price%20pressures%20have%20steadily%20eased%20over%20the%20past%20year%C2%A0%20as%20the%20Fed%20raised%20interest%20rates%20at%20the%20fastest%20pace%20in%20four%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20downside%20surprise%20in%20US%20June%20CPI%20inflation%20has%20seen%20the%20dollar%20drop%20to%20new%20lows%20for%20the%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20strategists%20at%20ING%20led%20by%20Chris%20Turner%20wrote%20in%20a%20note.%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20big%20dollar%20trend%2C%20this%20may%20be%20the%20start%20of%20the%20long-awaited%20cyclical%20decline.%20We%20prefer%20to%20run%20with%20the%20dollar%20bearish%20story%20for%20the%20time%20being%2C%20where%20DXY%20should%20press%20big%20psychological%20support%20at%20100.00.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dollar%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fdollar-weakness-currencies-dxy-federal-reserve-interest-rates-inflation-q1-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweakening%20since%20late%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20speculation%20cooling%20inflation%20will%20allow%20the%20US%20central%20bank%20to%20stop%20raising%20rates%2C%20or%20even%20start%20cutting%20them%20in%20the%20foreseeable%20future.%20Lower%20interest%20rates%20tend%20to%20make%20a%20currency%20less%20attractive%20to%20international%20investors%20who%20seek%20higher%20yields.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20has%20raised%20benchmark%20rates%20by%20500%20basis%20points%20since%20last%20spring%2C%20from%20near-zero%20levels%20to%20north%20of%205%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EING%20economist%20James%20Knightly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthink.ing.com%2Farticles%2Ffx-daily-dollar-drops-on-the-disinflation-trade%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20while%20inflation%20surprised%20on%20the%20goo