0my%20Instagram%20feed%20during%20the%20height%20of%20pandemic%20isolation.%20I%20thought%20the%20slick%2030-second%20video%20promising%20me%20a%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20easy%26quot%3B%20way%20to%20get%20ADHD%20medication%20was%20another%20gimmick.%20But%20after%20the%20algorithm%20pushed%20a%20few%20more%20plugs%20my%20way%2C%20I%20started%20to%20get%20curious.%20The%20drugs%2C%20to%20my%20surprise%2C%20were%20real.%20Unlike%20countless%20sketchy%20ads%20for%20black-market%20supplements%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcerebral-cuts-15-percent-staff-285-employees-layoffs-february-2023-2%5C%22%3ECerebral%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20then-hot%20telehealth%20startup%20behind%20the%20ads%2C%20offered%20a%20legal%20path%20to%20prescription%20medications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20indeed%20a%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20easy%26quot%3B%20path%20%E2%80%94%20too%20easy.%20My%20intake%20process%20to%20get%20prescribed%20a%20potentially%20addictive%20amphetamine%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20easier%20than%20getting%20Taylor%20Swift%20tickets%20or%20an%20appointment%20with%20my%20primary-care%20physician.%20Even%20as%20I%20doubted%20that%20I%20met%20the%20clinical%20criteria%20for%20ADHD%2C%20I%20could%20honestly%20answer%20the%20vague%2C%20brief%20self-assessment%20(e.g.%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20often%20do%20you%20have%20difficulty%20paying%20attention%20when%20you%20are%20doing%20boring%20or%20repetitive%20work%3F%26quot%3B)%20and%20receive%20the%20same%20result%20as%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20AI-targeted%20customers%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20some%20symptoms%20consistent%20with%20ADHD.%20We%20suggest%20further%20evaluation.%26quot%3B%20When%20I%20spoke%20to%20a%20Cerebral%20nurse%20practitioner%20for%20all%20of%2013%20minutes%2C%20the%20experience%20was%20much%20the%20same.%20Answering%20that%2C%20yes%2C%20my%20concentration%20was%20strained%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20once-in-a-century%20pandemic%20got%20me%20an%20official%20diagnosis%20and%20prescription.%20Like%20its%20many%20telehealth%20competitors%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.donefirst.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.klarityadhd.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKlarity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fadhdonline.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadhdonline.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.circlemedical.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECircle%20Medical%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3ECerebral%20could%20peddle%2C%20prescribe%2C%20and%20postmark%20a%20package%20of%20Adderall%20for%20me%20while%20I%20never%20left%20the%20couch.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20breed%20of%20direct-to-consumer%20services%20is%20aggressively%20using%20targeted%20ads%20to%20sell%20habit-forming%20medications.%20Not%20only%20do%20these%20companies%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20those%20seeking%20recreational%20drugs%20to%20access%20them%2C%20they're%20also%20poised%20to%20inundate%20and%20threaten%20the%20sobriety%20of%20people%20in%20recovery.%20And%20unlike%20a%20typical%20prescriber%20who%20might%20interrogate%20answers%20to%20assess%20genuine%20need%2C%20some%20of%20these%20firms%20appear%20to%20be%20designed%20to%20remove%20every%20possible%20barrier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20AI%20and%20surveillance%20capitalism%2C%20which%20empower%20today's%20targeted%20ads%2C%20have%20joined%20forces%20with%20the%20deadly%20OxyContin%20playbook.%20But%20unlike%20the%20opioid%20crisis%20of%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20advertisers%20today%20have%20much%20more%20data%20and%20far%20more%20precise%20tools%20to%20push%20prescriptions%2C%20and%20our%20privacy%20laws%20haven't%20even%20tried%20to%20keep%20up.%20Without%20intervention%2C%20another%20public-health%20catastrophe%20looms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Throwing%20antipsychotics%20around%20like%20candy'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20algorithm%20can't%20create%20addiction%20out%20of%20nothing%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20the%20crucial%20connector%20that%20lets%20companies%20reach%20those%20most%20at%20risk.%20Looking%20back%20on%20my%20Cerebral%20experience%20now%2C%20the%20similarities%20to%20the%20opioid%20crisis%20are%20clear.%20Having%20researched%20the%20rise%20of%20Purdue%20Pharma's%20OxyContin%20blight%2C%20the%20most%20pernicious%20catalyst%20was%20the%20same%20thing%20I%20saw%20in%20those%20Instagram%20ads%3A%20aggressive%2C%20data-driven%20marketing.%20As%20Dr.%20Art%20Van%20Zee%20wrote%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC2622774%2F%23bib4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Journal%20of%20Public%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202009%2C%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20cornerstones%20of%20Purdue's%20marketing%20plan%20was%20the%20use%20of%20sophisticated%20marketing%20data%20to%20influence%20physicians'%20prescribing.%26quot%3B%20The%20Sackler%20family's%20pharma%20giant%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20used%20%26quot%3Bprescriber%20profiles%20on%20individual%20physicians%20%E2%80%94%20detailing%20the%20prescribing%20patterns%20of%20physicians%20nationwide%20%E2%80%94%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20influence%20doctors'%20prescribing%20habits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOxyContin%20was%20pharmacologically%20unremarkable%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F14585554%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalogous%20to%20countless%20opioid%20medications%20that%20had%20been%20on%20the%20market%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fa%3E%20But%20Purdue%20discovered%20an%20ingenious%2C%20and%20calamitous%2C%20edge%3A%20harnessing%20data%20to%20target%20doctors%20with%20an%20onslaught%20of%20marketing%20materials%2C%20cajoling%20prescribers%20to%20hand%20out%20the%20medication%20more%20freely%2C%20and%20making%20the%20disastrous%20promise%20that%20their%20formulation%20was%20less%20addictive.%20It%20wasn't.%20OxyContin%20was%20patented%20in%201996%2C%20and%20Purdue's%20blitzkrieg%20marketing%20campaign%20began%20soon%20after%2C%20largely%20triggering%20the%20opioid%20epidemic.%20Between%201999%20and%202017%2C%20drug%20overdose%20deaths%20involving%20prescription%20opioids%20climbed%20from%20some%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnida.nih.gov%2Fresearch-topics%2Ftrends-statistics%2Foverdose-death-rates%23%3A~%3Atext%3DDrug%2520overdose%2520deaths%2520involving%2520prescription%2Cinvolving%2520prescription%2520opioids%2520totaled%252016%252C706.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3%2C000%20a%20year%20to%20more%20than%2017%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%202017%2C%20Purdue's%20annual%20revenue%20had%20grown%20to%20%2435%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20bankrupt%2C%20Purdue%20stands%20as%20a%20warning%20for%20any%20pharmaceutical%20company%20that%20would%20try%20to%20recruit%20physicians%20with%20the%20same%20predatory%20tactics%20%E2%80%94%20yet%20they%20persist.%20Just%20as%20important%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20believe%20that%20any%20doctor%20today%20would%20trust%20a%20pharmaceutical%20rep%20peddling%20pain%20meds%20with%20a%20similar%20claim.%20But%20online%20prescribers%20don't%20need%20to%20market%20to%20the%20doctor%2C%20because%20they%20%3Cem%3Eare%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20doctor%2C%20and%20patients%20are%20left%20with%20no%20one%20but%20themselves%20to%20look%20out%20for%20their%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EOnline%20prescribers%20don't%20need%20to%20market%20to%20the%20doctor%2C%20because%20they%20are%20the%20doctor%2C%20and%20patients%20are%20left%20with%20no%20one%20but%20themselves%20to%20look%20out%20for%20their%20well-being.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EPhysicians%20have%20already%20begun%20to%20warn%20that%20the%20Adderall%20crisis%20could%20repeat%20history.%20%26quot%3BThe%20prescription%20amphetamine%20crisis%20is%20growing%20and%20could%20catch%20up%20to%20the%20opioid%20epidemic%20in%20scope%20and%20damage%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.psychologytoday.com%2Fus%2Fblog%2Fwhere-science-meets-the-steps%2F201805%2Fwill-adderall-be-the-new-opioid-crisis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20David%20Sack%20wrote%20in%20%26quot%3BPsychology%20Today%26quot%3B%20in%202018.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20Canadian%20psychiatrist%20Anthony%20Yeung%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1177%2F07067437221082854%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20studied%3C%2Fa%3E%20misinformation%20in%20videos%20about%20ADHD%20on%20TikTok%20and%20found%20that%20deception%20is%20rampant.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20a%20doubt%20targeted%20ads%20(especially%20peak%20pandemic)%20have%20had%20an%20outsized%20impact%26quot%3B%20on%20Adderall%20prescription%20rates%2C%20he%20told%20me%2C%20though%20he%20noted%20researchers%20still%20struggle%20to%20access%20ad%20data%20on%20many%20platforms%2C%20so%20it%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20map%20out%20the%20precise%20effect.%20And%20while%20Adderall%20is%20what%20most%20fueled%20these%20telehealth%20firms'%20growth%20over%20the%20past%20three%20years%2C%20they%20also%20market%20a%20number%20of%20highly%20addictive%20medications.%20They%20are%20just%20as%20much%20a%20ticking%20time%20bomb%20for%20those%20addicted%20to%20sedatives%20like%20Xanax%20and%20other%20habit-forming%20medications.%3Cq%3E%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20AI-augmented%20advertising%2C%20finding%20yourself%20targeted%20only%20takes%20a%20single%20moment%20of%20engagement.%20After%20I%20first%20visited%20the%20Cerebral%20site%2C%20I%20was%20soon%20faced%20with%20dozens%20of%20ads.%20Some%20days%20it%20felt%20like%20they%20were%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20ads%20I%20saw%20on%20multiple%20social-media%20platforms.%20For%20me%2C%20the%20pattern%20was%20suspicious%2C%20but%20for%20someone%20struggling%20with%20addiction%2C%20it%20feels%20diabolical.%20These%20ads%20may%20overwhelm%20those%20in%20recovery%20%E2%80%94%20imagine%20trying%20to%20fight%20dependency%20and%20protect%20your%20health%20while%20these%20firms%20constantly%20bombard%20you%20with%20temptation.%20(On%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20the%20growing%20use%20of%20Adderall%20recreationally%20makes%20the%20medication%20far%20more%20difficult%20to%20find%20for%20those%20who%20actually%20have%20ADHD.%20In%202022%2C%20telehealth%20prescriptions%20accounted%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2F03%2F14%2Fadderall-shortage-telehealth-prescriptions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E40%25%20of%20all%20Adderall%20prescriptions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20driving%20record%20usage.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20nature%20of%20online%20advertising.%20This%20is%20why%20you%20see%20the%20same%20pair%20of%20shoes%20following%20you%20online%20from%20website%20to%20website%2C%20or%20why%20the%20trip%20you%20almost%20booked%20is%20constantly%20in%20your%20feed.%20Advertisers%20systematically%20target%20those%20who%20are%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20buying.%20A%20dollar%20spent%20on%20those%20who've%20shown%20interest%20is%20seen%20as%20far%20more%20valuable%20than%20a%20dollar%20spent%20on%20someone%20who%20may%20be%20a%20terrible%20fit%20for%20the%20product.%20But%20these%20companies%20have%20no%20way%20of%20knowing%20who's%20addicted%20or%20in%20recovery.%20Last%20year%2C%20a%20nurse%20practitioner%20warned%20Cerebral'%20s%20approach%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fcerebral-adderall-adhd-prescribe-11654705250%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Brisky%20because%20you%20really%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20who%20is%20drug%20seeking%20and%20who%20is%20really%20suffering%20from%20ADHD.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20Yann%20Poncin%2C%20a%20clinical%20child%20psychiatrist%20at%20the%20Yale%20School%20of%20Medicine%2C%20told%20me%20that%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20it%20gets%20to%20that%20level%20of%20targeted%20marketing%2C%20there's%20no%20way%20for%20people%20to%20know%20what%20other%20people%20are%20experiencing.%26quot%3B%20We%20as%20a%20society%20may%20have%20come%20to%20accept%20being%20stalked%20by%20targeted%20ads%2C%20but%20the%20consequences%20are%20much%20graver%20when%20the%20product%20itself%20is%20a%20danger.%20Getting%20hounded%20by%20that%20chew%20toy%20you%20thought%20of%20buying%20your%20shih%20tzu%20is%20one%20thing%3B%20getting%20harassed%20by%20a%20drug%20that%20mirrors%20methamphetamine%20is%20an%20entirely%20different%20matter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20scale%20is%20stunning.%20Last%20year%2C%20The%20Wall%20Street%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fcerebral-adderall-adhd-prescribe-11654705250%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20detailed%20how%20at%20one%20point%2C%20Cerebral's%20ad%20buy%20had%20become%20so%20immense%20it%20was%20the%20third-largest%20advertiser%20on%20TikTok.%20And%20as%20the%20company%20grew%2C%20employees%20became%20alarmed.%20Some%20worried%20that%20the%20platform%20could%20enable%20addiction.%20One%20nurse%20practitioner%20told%20Insider%20that%20employees%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftelehealth-startup-cerebral-prescribed-psych-meds-2022-6%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bwill%20just%20throw%20antipsychotics%20around%20like%20it's%20fucking%20candy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20Cerebral%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2F03%2F14%2Fadderall-shortage-telehealth-prescriptions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20that%20its%20%26quot%3Bclinicians%20exercise%20their%20independent%20professional%20judgment%20in%20diagnosing%20and%20treating%20their%20patients%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20that%20same%20Journal%20article%20reported%20that%20company%20leaders%20had%20urged%20employees%20to%20prescribe%20ADHD%20to%20100%25%20of%20patients%20without%20comorbidities.%20The%20company%20was%20far%20from%20alone%20in%20flooding%20the%20zone.%20In%20just%20four%20weeks%20last%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Ftelehealth-cerebral-done-ads-mental-health-adhd-11672161087%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20%20telehealth%20companies%20ran%20more%20than%202%2C100%20ads%3C%2Fa%3E%20promoting%20unapproved%20uses%20of%20prescription%20meds%20or%20failing%20to%20list%20their%20risks.%20As%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2F2022-03-11%2Fcerebral-app-over-prescribed-adhd-meds-ex-employees-say%3Fsref%3DXIzXWjPY%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20approach%20could%20accelerate%20the%20crises%20of%20people%20already%20dealing%20with%20complex%20mental-health%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBan%20targeted%20ads%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EConsequences%20for%20its%20hyperaggressive%20tactics%20have%20caught%20up%20with%20Cerebral.%20As%20the%20Journal%20reported%2C%20after%20ADHD%20medications%20grew%20to%2020%25%20of%20the%20VC-funded%20company's%20business%2C%20driving%20a%20%244.8%20billion%20valuation%2C%20things%20came%20crashing%20to%20earth.%20Cerebral's%20CEO%20was%20fired%2C%20many%20employees%20left%2C%20subpoenas%20from%20federal%20prosecutors%20were%20served%2C%20and%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20pharmacy%20partners%20stopped%20filling%20the%20company's%20prescriptions%2C%20prompting%20the%20company%20to%20stop%20offering%20ADHD%20drugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Cerebral's%20collapse%20is%20far%20from%20the%20end%20of%20this%20saga.%20The%20relaxed%20regulations%20that%20emerged%20during%20the%20COVID%20pandemic%20are%20a%20big%20part%20of%20the%20problem.%20Early%20in%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20Drug%20Enforcement%20Agency%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%20suspended%20the%20Ryan%20Haight%20Act%2C%20a%202008%20law%20that%20required%20telehealth%20providers%20to%20have%20at%20least%20one%20in-person%20session%20with%20a%20client%20before%20writing%20prescriptions%20for%20Schedule%202%20medications%2C%20which%20includes%20habit-forming%20medications%20like%20Adderall%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deadiversion.usdoj.gov%2Fschedules%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DExamples%2520of%2520Schedule%2520II%2520narcotics%2Copium%252C%2520codeine%252C%2520and%2520hydrocodone.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOxyContin%2C%20and%20Xanax%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20move%20made%20sense%20then%20but%20removed%20the%20guardrails%20to%20protect%20against%20the%20exact%20sort%20of%20abuses%20that%20led%20to%20the%20death%20of%20the%20Ryan%20Haight%20Act's%20namesake%2C%20a%20California%20teenager%20who%20overdosed%20on%20Vicodin%20that%20he%20was%20prescribed%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EWe%20as%20a%20society%20may%20have%20come%20to%20accept%20being%20stalked%20by%20targeted%20ads%2C%20but%20consequences%20are%20much%20graver%20when%20the%20product%20itself%20is%20a%20danger.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20the%20official%20end%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20public-health%20emergency%2C%20companies%20are%20still%20able%20to%20prescribe%20Schedule%202%20substances%20without%20an%20in-person%20visit.%20The%20suspension%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftelehealth.hhs.gov%2Fproviders%2Ftelehealth-policy%2Fprescribing-controlled-substances-via-telehealth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERyan%20Haight%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20currently%20set%20to%20expire%20on%20November%2011%2C%202023%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20guarantee%20that%20the%20rollback%20won't%20be%20delayed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interim%2C%20numerous%20competitors%20are%20jumping%20into%20the%20breach.%20In%20the%20course%20of%20researching%20this%20piece%2C%20I%20was%20served%20ads%20for%20ADHD%20medications%20from%20the%20rival%20telehealth%20startup%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.donefirst.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20friends%20sent%20me%20examples%20of%20targeted%20ads%20on%20Instagram%2C%20TikTok%2C%20and%20Twitter%20from%20firms%20offering%20everything%20from%20ADHD-care%20apps%20to%20Adderall%20and%20even%20psychedelics%20like%20ketamine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESadly%2C%20the%20solution%20isn't%20as%20simple%20as%20rolling%20back%20the%20regulations%20that%20allow%20companies%20to%20prescribe%20these%20drugs.%20Not%20only%20is%20telemedicine%20more%20convenient%2C%20it%20also%20offers%20a%20lifeline%20to%20millions%20of%20individuals%20without%20local%20access%20to%20care%20or%20who%20find%20it%20too%20expensive.%20Instead%2C%20we%20need%20a%20middle%20ground.%20Rather%20than%20restricting%20prescribers'%20ability%20to%20give%20medications%20remotely%2C%20we%20can%20focus%20on%20the%20promotional%20and%20sales%20tactics%20that%20set%20these%20firms%20apart%20from%20a%20family%20doctor%20who%20sees%20a%20patient%20over%20a%20video%20call.%20We%20can%20improve%20intake%20and%20assessment%20requirements.%20We%20can%20have%20automatic%20audits%20for%20firms%20with%20abnormally%20high%20levels%20of%20Schedule%202%20prescriptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20proposal%20Art%20Van%20Zee%20made%20to%20quell%20the%20OxyContin%20scourge%20in%202009%20would%20stand%20today%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20public%20health%20would%20be%20better%20protected%20if%20the%20FDA%20reviewed%20all%20advertising%20...%20for%20their%20truthfulness%2C%20accuracy%2C%20balance%2C%20and%20scientific%20validity%2C%20%3Cem%3Ebefore%3C%2Fem%3E%20dissemination.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20above%20all%2C%20we%20need%20rules%20that%20ban%20targeted%20ads%20for%20drugs%20that%20can%20get%20patients%20hooked.%20The%20United%20States%20and%20New%20Zealand%20are%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.health.harvard.edu%2Fmedications%2Fdo-not-get-sold-on-drug-advertising%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHow%2520drug%2520ads%2520work%2Cguidelines%2520relating%2520to%2520broadcast%2520media.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonly%20countries%20in%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20allow%20direct-to-consumer%20marketing%20for%20prescription%20drugs.%20No%20matter%20what%20safeguards%20are%20in%20place%2C%20as%20long%20as%20companies%20can%20combine%20them%2C%20habit-forming%20medications%20and%20AI%20ad%20targeting%20will%20make%20a%20deadly%20cocktail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Falbert-fox-cahn%5C%22%3EAlbert%20Fox%20Cahn%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20founder%20and%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Surveillance%20Technology%20Oversight%20Project%2C%20or%20S.T.O.P.%2C%20a%20New%20York-based%20civil-rights%20and%20privacy%20group.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-adderall-targeted-advertising-opioid-crisis-cerebral-purdue-pharma-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689240600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ac52986d7e02001af8b023%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-adderall-targeted-advertising-opioid-crisis-cerebral-purdue-pharma-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Online%20pill%20services%20are%20using%20AI%20to%20turbocharge%20the%20same%20aggressive%20marketing%20tactics%20that%20drove%20the%20opioid%20epidemic.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Albert%20Fox%20Cahn)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-adderall-targeted-advertising-opioid-crisis-cerebral-purdue-pharma-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%2