%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fenqgiu8g_delhi-flood_625x300_13_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdont-leave-house-if-arvind-kejriwal-makes-a-request-amid-delhi-flooding-4203470%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Due%20to%20the%20rise%20in%20the%20water%20level%20of%20Yamuna%2C%20traffic%20movement%20has%20been%20severely%20hit%20in%20several%20parts%20of%20Delhi.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdont-leave-house-if-arvind-kejriwal-makes-a-request-amid-delhi-flooding-4203470%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdont-leave-house-if-arvind-kejriwal-makes-a-request-amid-delhi-flooding-4203470%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdont-leave-house-if-arvind-kejriwal-makes-a-request-amid-delhi-flooding-4203470%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22More%20Than%20Half%20The%20World's%20Oceans%20Have%20Changed%20Colour.%20Read%20Why%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20colour%20of%20over%2056%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20world's%20oceans%2C%20larger%20than%20Earth's%20total%20land%20expanse%2C%20has%20changed%20significantly%20over%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20and%20human-caused%20climate%20change%20is%20likely%20the%20driver%2C%20according%20to%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20colour%20changes%2C%20subtle%20to%20the%20human%20eye%2C%20cannot%20be%20explained%20by%20natural%2C%20year-to-year%20variability%20alone%2C%20the%20researchers%20from%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(MIT)%2C%20US%2C%20and%20other%20institutes%20write%20in%20their%20paper%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOcean%20colour%2C%20a%20literal%20reflection%20of%20the%20life%20and%20materials%20in%20its%20waters%2C%20in%20regions%20near%20the%20equator%20was%20found%20to%20have%20steadily%20turned%20greener%20over%20time%2C%20indicating%20changes%20in%20the%20ecosystems%20within%20the%20surface%20oceans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20green%20colour%20of%20the%20ocean%20waters%20comes%20from%20the%20green%20pigment%20chlorophyll%20present%20in%20phytoplankton%2C%20the%20plant-like%20microbes%20abundant%20in%20upper%20ocean.%20Scientists%20are%2C%20therefore%2C%20keen%20to%20monitor%20phytoplankton%20to%20see%20their%20response%20to%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20authors%20of%20this%20study%20showed%20through%20previous%20studies%20that%20it%20would%20take%2030%20years%20of%20tracking%20chlorophyll%20changes%20before%20climate-change-driven%20trends%20would%20show%2C%20because%20natural%2C%20annual%20variations%20in%20chlorophyll%20would%20overwhelm%20those%20influenced%20by%20human%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202019%20paper%2C%20study%20co-author%20Stephanie%20Dutkiewicz%20and%20her%20colleagues%20showed%20that%20monitoring%20other%20ocean%20colours%2C%20whose%20annual%20variations%20are%20much%20smaller%20than%20those%20of%20chlorophyll%2C%20would%20convey%20more%20clear%20signals%20of%20climate-change-driven%20changes%20and%20that%20they%20might%20even%20be%20apparent%20in%2020%20years%2C%20rather%20than%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20worth%20looking%20at%20the%20whole%20spectrum%2C%20rather%20than%20just%20trying%20to%20estimate%20one%20number%20from%20bits%20of%20the%20spectrum%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20lead%20author%20B.%20B.%20Cael%20of%20the%20National%20Oceanography%20Center.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECael%20and%20team%20then%20statistically%20analysed%20all%20the%20seven%20ocean%20colours%20recorded%20by%20satellite%20observations%20from%202002%20to%202022%20together.%20He%20initially%20studied%20the%20colours'%20natural%20variations%20by%20seeing%20how%20they%20changed%20regionally%20in%20a%20given%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20observed%20how%20these%20annual%20variations%20changed%20over%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20climate%20change's%20contribution%20to%20all%20these%20changes%2C%20he%20used%20Dutkiewicz's%202019%20model%20to%20simulate%20the%20Earth's%20oceans%20under%20two%20scenarios%20-%20one%20with%20greenhouse%20gases%20and%20the%20other%20without%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20greenhouse-gas%20model%20predicted%20changes%20to%20the%20colour%20of%20about%2050%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20world's%20surface%20oceans%20in%20under%2020%20years%20-%20close%20to%20Cael's%20conclusions%20from%20his%20real-world%20satellite%20data%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20suggests%20that%20the%20trends%20we%20observe%20are%20not%20a%20random%20variation%20in%20the%20Earth%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cael.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20consistent%20with%20anthropogenic%20climate%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20running%20simulations%20that%20have%20been%20telling%20me%20for%20years%20that%20these%20changes%20in%20ocean%20colour%20are%20going%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dutkiewicz%2C%20senior%20research%20scientist%20in%20MIT's%20Department%20of%20Earth%2C%20Atmospheric%20and%20Planetary%20Sciences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20actually%20see%20it%20happening%20for%20real%20is%20not%20surprising%2C%20but%20frightening.%20And%20these%20changes%20are%20consistent%20with%20man-induced%20changes%20to%20our%20climate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689239820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F5t2ebq0c_ocean-generic-ocean-colour-change-generic-pixabay_625x300_13_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmore-than-half-the-worlds-oceans-have-changed-colour-read-why-4203238%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20colo