com%2F64aefb2494be880019f3a7f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22878%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVanessa%20Garcia%20works%20as%20a%20TaskRabbit%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%3Cp%3EVanessa%20Garcia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EVanessa%20Garcia%20works%20as%20a%20Taskrabbit%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20charging%20%2475%20an%20hour.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EShe%20helps%20people%20going%20through%20breakups%20organize%20their%20homes%20and%20they%20frequently%20open%20up%20to%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EGarcia%20says%20that%20clients%20often%20want%20to%20know%20its%20okay%20to%20let%20things%20go.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Vanessa%20Garcia%2C%20a%2029-year-old%20who%20works%20as%20a%20Taskrabbit%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20California.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20worked%20as%20a%20Taskrabbit%20for%20five%20years%20and%20in%20that%20time%2C%20I've%20helped%20people%20with%20a%20thousand%20little%20jobs%20%E2%80%93%20from%20personal%20assistant%20work%20to%20running%20errands%20to%20decorating%20%E2%80%93%20and%20can%20make%20anywhere%20from%20%244%2C000%20to%20%249%2C000%20per%20month.%20I%20normally%20charge%20%2475%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20I%20didn't%20expect%20was%20how%20many%20times%20I'd%20help%20people%20through%20a%20breakup.%20When%20people%20hire%20me%20after%20a%20breakup%20or%20even%20a%20divorce%2C%20they%20don't%20usually%20tell%20me%20up%20front%20what%20the%20situation%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20going%20into%20someone's%20home%20and%20helping%20them%20with%20organizational%20tasks%20is%20a%20really%20intimate%20thing%20and%20I%20try%20to%20be%20really%20friendly%20and%20open.%20That%20can%20lead%20to%20them%20telling%20me%20about%20the%20catalyst%20to%20my%20arrival.%20I've%20had%20people%20say%2C%20oh%2C%20I%20just%20got%20broken%20up%20with%2C%20or%20I'm%20ending%20a%20years-long%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20can%20kind%20of%20tell%20how%20much%20the%20breakup%20has%20affected%20them%20by%20the%20state%20of%20their%20house%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20home%20is%20a%20reflection%20of%20your%20mental%20and%20emotional%20state%20and%20if%20someone%20has%20been%20totally%20rocked%20by%20a%20break-up%2C%20their%20space%20tends%20to%20be%20really%20messy%20and%20sometimes%20even%20dirty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20there's%20trash%20everywhere%20and%20the%20person%20will%20say%20something%20like%20'I've%20really%20been%20going%20through%20it%20and%20I%20haven't%20been%20able%20to%20bring%20myself%20to%20lift%20a%20finger%20around%20here.'%20I%20really%20do%20my%20best%20to%20stay%20as%20nonjudgmental%20as%20possible.%20Everyone%20is%20going%20through%20their%20own%20struggles%20and%20I'm%20there%20to%20help%2C%20not%20to%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I'm%20done%20with%20my%20work%20and%20everything%20is%20organized%20and%20put%20away%2C%20it%20can%20feel%20like%20a%20clean%20slate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EClients%20tend%20to%20hang%20around%20while%20I%20organize%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20often%20talk%20about%20the%20relationship%20and%20what%20went%20wrong.%20Once%20or%20twice%20they've%20even%20cried.%20I've%20had%20clients%20tell%20me%20I%20should%20charge%20more%20because%20they%20got%20a%20therapy%20session%20out%20of%20the%20organization%20too%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20sweet.%20I%20like%20to%20think%20I'm%20helping%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20through%20something%20like%20a%20breakup%20is%20hard%20enough%20emotionally%20without%20a%20stranger%20coming%20into%20your%20space.%20I%20want%20them%20to%20feel%20as%20comfortable%20as%20possible%20and%20to%20feel%20that%20I've%20really%20provided%20a%20service%20for%20them.%20Sometimes%20it%20goes%20too%20well%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20client%20who%20asked%20me%20out%20on%20a%20date%20after%20I%20helped