GPT's%20initial%20release%2C%20OpenAI%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fblog%2Fchatgpt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewarned%20users%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20blog%20post%20that%20the%20chatbot%20would%20%26quot%3Bsometimes%20respond%20to%20harmful%20instructions%20or%20exhibit%20biased%20behavior.%26quot%3B%20The%20company%20assured%20then%20that%20it%20was%20moving%20to%20%26quot%3Bblock%20certain%20types%20of%20unsafe%20content%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20that%20it%20did%20expect%20the%20chatbot%20%26quot%3Bto%20have%20some%20false%20negatives%20and%20positives%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20time%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20acknowledged%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altmans-chatgpt-has-a-bias-problem-that-could-get-it-canceled-2023-2%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20tweet%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20ChatGPT%20has%20%26quot%3Bshortcomings%20around%20bias%26quot%3B%20and%20vowed%20the%20company%20would%20improve%20them.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20optimistic%20that%20we%20will%20get%20to%20a%20world%20where%20these%20models%20can%20be%20a%20force%20to%20reduce%20bias%20in%20society%2C%20not%20reinforce%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Altman%20said%20in%20a%20May%20interview%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frestofworld.org%2F2023%2F3-minutes-with-sam-altman%2F%5C%22%3Ewith%20Rest%20of%20World.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-detector-mislabels-essays-non-native-english-speakers-openai-chatgpt-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689238620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64aed8b094be880019f39fcf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-detector-mislabels-essays-non-native-english-speakers-openai-chatgpt-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20GPT-detection%20systems%