0bench%20to%20observe%20that%20it%20had%20little%20power%20over%20amendments%20to%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20Act%20and%20Delhi%20Special%20Police%20Establishment%20Act%2C%C2%A0to%20bring%20which%20the%20government%20promulgated%20an%20ordinance%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20amendments%20ensured%20the%20tenure%20of%20ED%20and%20CBI%20chiefs%20could%20be%20extended%20by%20up%20to%20three%20years%20after%20the%20mandated%20term%20of%20two%20years.%20The%20government%20brought%20these%20changes%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20already%20ordered%20it%20to%20not%20give%20the%20ED%20chief%20further%20extensions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnion%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Famit-shah-opposition-supreme-court-delusional-ed-congress-tmc%5C%22%3Etweet%3C%2Fa%3E%20pushing%20this%20verdict%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20victory%20%E2%80%93%20and%20what%20this%20could%20mean%20%E2%80%93%20was%20also%20a%20topic%20in%20some%20editorials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Undermining%20autonomy%3A%20On%20judicial%20endorsement%20of%20a%20tenure%20extension%20system%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fundermining-autonomy-the-hindu-editorial-on-judicial-endorsement-of-a-tenure-extension-system%2Farticle67071808.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20one%20paper%20which%20took%20a%20critical%20view%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20backing%20the%20amendments%20to%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20Act%20and%20Delhi%20Special%20Police%20Establishment%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20called%20the%20verdict%20%E2%80%9Ca%20setback%20to%20the%20cause%20of%20protecting%20their%20institutional%20independence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20welcoming%20the%20quashing%20of%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20extensions%2C%20the%20paper%20said%20that%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20verdict%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfree%20pass%20to%20the%20government%20to%20undermine%20the%20autonomy%20of%20these%20agencies.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20editorial%20says%2C%20the%20heads%20of%20the%20CBI%20and%20ED%20have%20an%20assured%20term%20of%20two%20years%20regardless%20of%20superannuation%2C%20and%20the%20introduction%20of%20a%20power%20to%20extend%20it%20to%20five%20years%20means%20an%20officer%20may%20get%20up%20to%20three%20annual%20extensions.%20As%20the%20petitioners%20who%20challenged%20the%20extension%20given%20to%20Mishra%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20court-appointed%20amicus%20curiae%20had%20argued%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20cited%2C%20%E2%80%9Cpiecemeal%20extensions%20undermine%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20office%2C%20and%20encourage%20a%20carrot-and-stick%20policy%20to%20make%20Directors%20toe%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20line.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20criticises%20court%E2%80%99s%20move%20to%20reject%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20contention%20that%20the%20changes%20to%20the%20Acts%20go%20against%20the%20spirit%20of%20earlier%20judgments%20that%20mandated%20fixed%20tenures%20to%20the%20CBI%20and%20ED%20heads%20to%20insulate%20them%20from%20extraneous%20pressures.%20It%20says%20that%20such%20a%20rejection%20also%20came%20without%20much%20justification.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20noted%20that%20contrasted%20with%20the%20criticism%20of%20partisan%20behaviour%20against%20these%20government%20agencies%2C%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20endorsement%20is%20not%20conducive%20to%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20finding%20that%20the%20amendments%20do%20not%20violate%20any%20fundamental%20rights%20is%20quite%20surprising%2C%20as%20allowing%20the%20government%20to%20have%20Directors%20who%20can%20pick%20and%20choose%20what%20cases%20to%20investigate%20based%20on%20political%20instructions%20certainly%20offends%20the%20rights%20of%20citizens%20to%20equal%20treatment%20and%20impartial%20investigation.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20there%20is%20a%20cloud%20of%20suspicion%20over%20the%20misuse%20of%20government%20agencies%20against%20political%20opponents%2C%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20endorsement%20of%20a%20tenure%20extension%20system%20designed%20to%20undermine%20their%20independence%20is%20not%20conducive%20to%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Extension%20row%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Tribune%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tribuneindia.com%2Fnews%2Feditorials%2Fextension-row-525123%3F_gl%3D1*17xm7cx*_ga*OUJWNVBJbWNyV25nSlBsSy1ONHk2QkVDS3lXaXVOWi1mMzFhdFdUdE5mVHdqZ3FQd0xqREZpMjJnU0VidnA0dg%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20in%20May%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20rapped%20the%20government%20for%20granting%20a%20third%20extension%20to%20Mishra%2C%20while%20wondering%20what%20made%20the%20officer%20%E2%80%98so%20indispensable%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20noted%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20had%20claimed%20that%20his%20continuation%20was%20%E2%80%9Cvital%20in%20view%20of%20the%20peer%20review%20being%20conducted%20by%20the%20Financial%20Action%20Task%20Force%20later%20this%20year.%E2%80%9D%20The%20government%20chose%20to%20retain%20Mishra%20at%20the%20helm%20even%20though%20the%20apex%20court%20had%20issued%20a%20mandamus%20that%20no%20further%20extension%20shall%20be%20granted%20to%20him%2C%20%3Cem%3ETribune%3C%2Fem%3E%20highlighted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsk-mishra-enforcement-directorate-fatf-evaluation%5C%22%3EAt%20SC%2C%20Modi%20Govt%20Justified%20S.K.%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20Extension%20Citing%20FATF%20Review.%20How%20Key%20Is%20His%20Role%20in%20it%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tribuneindia.com%2Fnews%2Feditorials%2Fextension-row-525123%3F_gl%3D1*17xm7cx*_ga*OUJWNVBJbWNyV25nSlBsSy1ONHk2QkVDS3lXaXVOWi1mM