ng-on-ed-chief-extensions-1236436.html%5C%22%3Eupheld%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20noted%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20upholding%20of%20the%20amendments%2C%20highlighting%20that%20they%20were%20made%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20%E2%80%9Cto%20counter%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judgement%20in%202021%20which%20barred%20any%20further%20extension%20to%20Mishra%2C%20who%20was%20already%20on%20an%20extended%20tenure.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20further%20stressed%20that%20these%20amendments%20%E2%80%9Ccould%20be%20misused%20to%20keep%20favoured%20officers%20in%20the%20two%20crucial%20positions%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20a%20fact%20which%20was%20pointed%20out%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20safeguards%20the%20court%20cited%20were%20not%20effective%2C%20%3Cem%3EDH%3C%2Fem%3E%20observed.%20Also%2C%20crucially%2C%20it%20said%2C%20what%20while%20the%20court%20said%20it%20could%20not%20sit%20in%20judgement%20over%20the%20merit%20of%20a%20law%20which%20parliament%20has%20passed%20in%20its%20wisdom%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20power%20of%20judicial%20review%20exists%20precisely%20for%20that%20reason.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20is%20one%20of%20the%20rare%20ones%20to%20point%20out%20that%20the%20response%20of%20the%20government%20to%20the%20judgement%20reflects%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20reality%20of%2C%20and%20further%20potential%20for%2C%20the%20use%20of%20its%20power%20by%20the%20government%20to%20control%20the%20agency.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20cited%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20response%20on%20Twitter%2C%20saying%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthose%20who%20were%20rejoicing%20over%20the%20judgement%E2%80%9D%20were%20delusional%20because%20the%20ED%20as%20an%20institution%20is%20not%20dependent%20on%20an%20individual.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPowers%20of%20the%20ED%20to%20strike%20at%20those%20who%20are%20corrupt%20and%20on%20the%20wrong%20side%20of%20the%20law%20remain%20the%20same.%20ED%20is%20an%20institution%20which%20rises%20beyond%20any%20one%20individual%20and%20is%20focused%20on%20achieving%20its%20core%20objective%20%E2%80%93%20i.e.%20to%20investigate%20offences%20of%20money%20laundering%20and%20violations%20of%20foreign%20exchange%20laws%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThose%20rejoicing%20over%20the%20Hon'ble%20SC%20decision%20on%20the%20ED%20case%20are%20delusional%20for%20various%20reasons%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amendments%20to%20the%20CVC%20Act%2C%20which%20were%20duly%20passed%20by%20the%20Parliament%2C%20have%20been%20upheld.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPowers%20of%20the%20ED%20to%20strike%20at%20those%20who%20are%20corrupt%20and%20on%20the%20wrong%20side%20of%20the%20law%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Amit%20Shah%20(%40AmitShah)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAmitShah%2Fstatus%2F1678765988702203905%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2011%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShah%20was%20clearly%20making%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20investigations%20and%20cases%20against%20many%20political%20leaders.%20By%20making%20that%20declaration%20Shah%20has%20confirmed%20the%20criticism%20against%20the%20ED%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20government%20has%20been%20using%20the%20agency%20against%20its%20political%20opponents%20and%20critics.%20The%20reference%20to%20%E2%80%9Centitled%20dynasts%E2%80%9D%20makes%20it%20clear%20who%20the%20targets%20are%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20editorial%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20stressed%20that%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20avowal%20of%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20policy%20is%20%E2%80%9Codd.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20ED%20is%20a%20statutory%20body%20with%20functions%20that%20it%20is%20expected%20to%20carry%20out%20without%20regard%20to%20the%20wishes%20of%20those%20in%20government.%20A%20member%20of%20the%20government%20has%20no%20reason%20or%20authority%20to%20speak%20on%20its%20behalf.%20The%20Home%20Minister%2C%20especially%2C%20has%20no%20reason%20to%20do%20so%20because%20the%20ED%20is%20attached%20to%20the%20Finance%20Ministry%2C%20not%20the%20Home%20Ministry.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20noted%20that%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20statement%20will%20%E2%80%9Ctherefore%20be%20taken%20as%20a%20reminder%20of%20the%20reality%20that%20the%20power%20of%20the%20ED%20actually%20rests%20with%20the%20government%2C%20and%20not%20with%20the%20Director%20of%20the%20agency.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20why%2C%20it%20says%2C%20opposition%20parties%20have%20taken%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20statement%20as%20a%20threat%20and%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdeclaration%20that%20the%20ED%20will%20not%20change%20its%20ways.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98State%E2%80%99s%20strong%20arm%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%20noted%20in%20its%20editorial%20that%20by%20all%20accounts%2C%20in%20its%20order%2C%20the%20three-judge%20bench%20has%20%E2%80%9Csought%20to%20distinguish%20the%20principle%20that%20gives%20parliament%20the%20privilege%20to%20amend%20laws%20from%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20it%20has%20exercised%20that%20privilege.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20editorial%20meditated%20upon%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20careful%20move%20to%20separate%20procedural%20and%20political%20strands%20in%20the%20challenge%20to%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20appointment%20and%20read%20the%20law%20back%20to%20the%20former.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20the%20court%20has%20cited%20self-imposed%20limits%20in%20the%20judicial%20review%20of%20legislative%20or%20executive%20actions%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20case%20of%20the%20amendments%20under%20challenge%2C%20the%20Court%20said%20while%20Parliament%20had%20the%20power%20to%20make%20them%20it%20did%20not%20grant%20arbitrary%20power%20to%20the%20government%20to%20extend%20the%20term%20of%20the%20ED%20or%20CBI%20director%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20editorial%20observed%2C%20then%20describing%20in%20detail%20how%20in%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20the%20government%20had%20extended%20his%20tenure%20multiple%20times%2C%20despite%20a%20court%20direction%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20editorial%20also%20pointed%20out%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%C2%A0response%20and%20said%20it%20%E2%80%9Cbrought%20into%20sharp%20relief%20the%20questionable%20politics%20that%20has%20shadowed%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20tenure.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUnder%20Mishra%2C%20many%20Opposition%20leaders%20had%20come%20under%20the%20lens%20of%20the%20ED.%20The%20Opposition%20sought%20relief%20from%20the%20SC%2C%20but%20the%20latter%20declined%20to%20entertain%20its%20plea%20that%20alleged%20%E2%80%9Cselected%20and%20targeted%E2%80%9D%20use%20of%20agencies%20by%20the%20central%20government.%20The%20onus%20is%20also%20on%20the%20agency%20to%20convince%20its%20critics%20that%20it%20is%20transparent%20and%20fair%20in%20its%20functioning%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689229838000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13115754%2FUntitled-design-19-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fsuprem-court-enforcement-directorate-sk-mishra-amit-shah-editorials%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20response%20after%20the%20Court%20order%20brought%20into%20sharp%20relief%20the%20questionable%20politics%20that%20has%20shadowed%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20tenure.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fsuprem-court-enforcement-directorate-sk-mishra-amit-shah-editorials%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Celeb%20looks%20that%20prove%20green%20is%20in%20this%20season%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689229800000%2C%22visual%