nfirmed%20to%20Russian%20state%20TV%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20Tsokov%20was%20killed.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETsokov%20was%20the%20deputy%20commander%20of%20Russia's%20southern%20military%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Gen.%20Sergei%20Surovikin%20has%20been%20missing%20since%20the%20Wagner%20Group's%20short-lived%20rebellion%20in%20late%20June%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20Russia's%20operations%20in%20Ukraine%20from%20October%202022%20to%20January%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fjan%2F12%2Fvladimir-putin-military-reshuffle-more-about-politics-than-a-change-of-strategy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euntil%20Gerasimov%20assumed%20command.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Surovikin%20was%20then%20designated%20as%20one%20of%20Gerasimov's%20three%20deputies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20on%20Wednesday%20about%20Surovikin's%20whereabouts%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Russian%20Duma's%20defense%20committee%2C%20Andrei%20Kartapolov%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.me%2Fshot_shot%2F54031%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20a%20reporter%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Btaking%20a%20rest%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20%26quot%3Bunavailable%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F06%2F27%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Frussian-general-prigozhin-rebellion.html%5C%22%3EThe%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-general-knew-about-wagner-uprising-plan-bad-putin-nyt-2023-6%5C%22%3ESurovikin%20knew%20of%20Wagner's%20mutiny%20before%20it%20happened.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fivan-popov-russian-general-ukraine-fired-feedback-boss-decapitating-kremlin-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C