cans-accusations%2Famp_articleshow%2F101715630.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'UCC%20Is%20Merely%20an%20Attempt%20to%20Undo%20the%20Existing%20Muslim%20Law%2C%20Sixth%20Schedule%20Laws'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F19120045%2FA_ritual_at_marriage_ceremony.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20its%20submission%20to%20the%20Law%20Commission%20of%20India%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Democratic%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Association%20(AIDWA)%20has%20said%20that%20a%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20(UCC)%20alone%20will%20not%20result%20in%20women%20getting%20equal%20rights%2C%20as%20uniformity%20does%20not%20mean%20equality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20from%20the%20organisation%E2%80%99s%20experience%20of%20dealing%20with%20personal%20laws%20and%20actively%20engaging%20in%20previous%20reform%20measures%2C%20the%20submission%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20strongly%20feel%20that%20the%20UCC%20is%20merely%20an%20attempt%20to%20undo%20the%20existing%20Muslim%20Law%20and%20laws%20which%20come%20under%20the%20Sixth%20Schedule%2C%20pertaining%20to%20the%20tribal%20areas.%20In%20keeping%20with%20democratic%20norms%2C%20this%20can%20only%20be%20done%20after%20extensive%20discussions%20with%20the%20communities%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6We%20apprehend%20that%20on%20the%20pretext%20of%20re-examining%20the%20need%20for%20a%20UCC%2C%20the%20effort%20will%20largely%20be%20to%20bring%20in%20uniform%20laws%20which%20will%20be%20majoritarian%20laws%2C%20and%20not%20laws%20which%20give%20substantive%20equal%20rights%20to%20women.%20As%20said%20earlier%2C%20uniformity%20of%20law%20by%20itself%20will%20not%20result%20in%20equality%20for%20women%2C%20and%20in%20fact%20will%20probably%20result%20in%20duplicating%20Hindu%20laws%20and%20its%20gender%20biases%20on%20all%20communities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAIDWA%20has%20also%20asked%20why%20the%20Law%20Commission%20is%20once%20again%20opening%20up%20the%20UCC%20debate%20and%20asking%20for%20public%20opinion%2C%20since%20%E2%80%9Cthe%2021%3Csup%3Est%3C%2Fsup%3E%20Law%20Commission%2C%20in%202018%2C%20had%20also%20agreed%20with%20our%20view%20that%20a%20UCC%20was%20neither%20desirable%20or%20necessary%20to%20align%20personal%20law%20with%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20women%20including%20substantive%20equality%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20text%20of%20AIDWA%E2%80%99s%20submission%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETo%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Member%20Secretary%2C%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3ELaw%20Commission%20of%20India%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E4%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%20floor%2C%20Lok%20Nayak%20Bhavan%2C%3Cbr%3E%5CnKhan%20Market%2C%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20with%20reference%20to%20the%20Public%20Notice%20issued%20by%20you%20on%20the%2014%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%20of%20June%202023%20eliciting%20views%20on%20the%20need%20for%20a%20UCC%20again.%20We%20write%20to%20you%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Democratic%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Association%20(AIDWA)%2C%20a%20women%E2%80%99s%20organization%20with%20a%20membership%20of%20more%20than%20a%20crore%20across%20the%20country.%20Women%20in%20our%20country%20have%20been%20suffering%20for%20centuries%20under%20the%20burden%20of%20patriarchal%20and%20discriminatory%20personal%20laws%20in%20all%20religious%20communities.%20We%20are%20not%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20UCC%20as%20just%20having%20uniform%20laws%20will%20not%20result%20in%20women%20getting%20equal%20rights%20or%20in%20wiping%20out%20the%20discrimination%20inherent%2C%20in%20various%20degrees%2C%20in%20these%20laws.%20This%20is%20because%20uniformity%20per%20se%20does%20not%20mean%20equality%20and%20cannot%20be%20equated%20with%20equality%20and%20justice%20for%20women.%20We%20also%20feel%20that%20uniformity%20is%20neither%20necessary%20nor%20desirable%20in%20India%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22BJP's%20Clamour%20for%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20Driven%20by%20Aim%20of%20Dividing%2C%20Not%20Uniting%2C%20Indians%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjps-clamour-for-uniform-civil-code-driven-by-aim-of-dividing-not-uniting-indians%5C%22%3EBJP%E2%80%99s%20Clamour%20for%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20Driven%20by%20Aim%20of%20Dividing%2C%20Not%20Uniting%2C%20Indians%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20organization%20has%20dealt%20with%20issues%20of%20personal%20law%20for%20the%20last%2040%20years%20and%20is%20actively%20engaged%20in%20each%20State%20in%20dealing%20with%20personal%20law%20cases%20of%20women%20in%20various%20Legal%20Cells.%20AIDWA%20has%20unequivocally%20stood%20for%20reform%20and%20for%20equality%20and%20non-discrimination%20in%20each%20personal%20law%20and%20has%20campaigned%20for%20reform%20in%20the%20personal%20laws%20of%20all%20communities.%20For%20instance%2C%20amongst%20other%20reforms%2C%20it%20has%20actively%20participated%20in%20bringing%20about%20reform%20in%20the%20Hindu%20Succession%20Act%3B%20in%20the%20Indian%20Divorce%20Act%20relating%20to%20Christians%20and%20in%20the%20campaign%20against%20Triple%20Talak.%20All%20these%20reform%20efforts%20have%20taken%20place%20along%20with%20and%20in%20consultation%20with%20members%20of%20the%20various%20communities%20particularly%20women%20of%20these%20communities.%20%C2%A0AIDWA%20has%20followed%20a%20two-pronged%20strategy%20of%20supporting%20reforms%20within%20each%20community%20and%20in%20bringing%20about%20common%20laws%20where%20there%20is%20a%20gap%20in%20personal%20laws%20or%20when%20such%20laws%20are%20necessary%20to%20do%20justice%20to%20women.%20Thus%2C%20AIDWA%20has%20participated%20in%20the%20struggle%20for%20and%20supported%20the%20reforms%20in%20Dowry%20Laws%2C%20The%20Prohibition%20of%20Child%20Marriage%20Act%2C%20the%20Law%20against%20Sexual%20Harassment%20at%20the%20Work%20Place%20and%20the%20Law%20against%20Domestic%20Violence%20which%20also%20gives%20the%20right%20to%20residence%20and%20monetary%20compensation%2C%20apart%20from%20other%20Laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20surprised%20that%20the%2022%3Csup%3End%3C%2Fsup%3E%20Law%20Commission%20is%20again%20examining%20the%20issue%20of%20a%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20as%20the%2021%3Csup%3Est%3C%2Fsup%3E%20Law%20Commission%20had%20already%20categorically%20expressed%20its%20views%20against%20it.%20The%2021%3Csup%3Est%3C%2Fsup%3E%20Law%20Commission%2C%20in%202018%2C%20had%20also%20agreed%20with%20our%20view%20that%20a%20UCC%20was%20neither%20desirable%20or%20necessary%20to%20align%20personal%20law%20with%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20women%20including%20substantive%20equality.%20The%2021%3Csup%3Est%3C%2Fsup%3E%20Law%20Commission%20had%20taken%20extensive%20evidence%20on%20the%20issue%2C%20carried%20out%20extensive%20research%2C%20participated%20in%20many%20seminars%20and%20discussions%2C%20and%20had%20then%20opined%20that%20the%20time%20was%20not%20ripe%20for%20a%20UCC%20as%20stated%20below%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CVarious%20aspects%20of%20prevailing%20personal%20laws%20deprivilege%20women.%20This%20Commission%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20it%20is%20discrimination%20and%20not%20difference%20which%20lies%20at%20the%20root%20of%20inequality.%20In%20order%20to%20address%20this%20inequality%2C%20the%20Commission%20has%20suggested%20a%20range%20of%20amendments%20to%20existing%20family%20laws%20%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%20This%20Commission%20has%20therefore%20dealt%20with%20laws%20that%20are%20discriminatory%20rather%20than%20providing%20a%20uniform%20civil%20code%20which%20is%20neither%20necessary%20nor%20desirable%20at%20this%20stage.%20Most%20countries%20are%20now%20moving%20towards%20recognition%20of%20difference%2C%20and%20the%20mere%20existence%20of%20difference%20does%20not%20imply%20discrimination%2C%20but%20is%20indicative%20of%20a%20robust%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20do%20not%20understand%20the%20need%20to%20engage%20in%20this%20exercise%20again%20through%20a%20vaguely%20worded%20notice%20which%20provides%20no%20blueprint%20of%20what%20the%20Law%20Commission%20has%20conceptualized.%20Further%2C%20by%20asking%20for%20opinions%20within%20an%20extremely%20limited%20period%20of%20a%20month%20we%20feel%20that%20this%20is%20not%20a%20serious%20attempt%20to%20get%20the%20opinions%20of%20various%20organizations%20and%20people%20working%20on%20the%20issue%2C%20but%20is%20just%20a%20formality.%20It%20seems%20that%20the%20Law%20Commission%20has%20an%20agenda%20to%20somehow%20recommend%20a%20UCC%20as%20the%20BJP%20Government%20of%20various%20States%20and%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20himself%20has%20recently%20spoken%20in%20favour%20of%20it.%20We%20are%20also%20surprised%20that%20the%20Law%20Commission%20has%20specifically%20asked%20only%20various%20religious%20bodies%20for%20their%20opinion.%20The%20UCC%20is%20an%20issue%20which%20concerns%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20and%20equality%20and%20the%20Law%20Commission%20should%20prioritize%20all%20those%20working%20on%20the%20issue%20including%20women%20of%20the%20communities.%20The%20present%20exercise%20therefore%20to%20re-examine%20the%20issue%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20the%20government%20is%20to%20bring%20about%20a%20UCC%20against%20the%20wishes%20of%20most%20women%E2%80%99s%20organizations%20and%20groups%20and%20the%20minority%20communities%20who%20had%20not%20asked%20for%20it.%20It%20is%20clear%20that%20this%20agenda%20is%20also%20being%20actively%20pursued%20by%20various%20BJP%20led%20governments%20in%20States%20like%20Uttarakhand%20who%20have%20openly%20declared%20their%20intention%20to%20bring%20about%20a%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22BJP%20Equates%20UCC%20With%20Gender%20Justice.%20But%20Can%20It%20End%20Discrimination%20In-Built%20in%20Personal%20Laws%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fbjp-ucc-with-gender-justice-discrimination-personal-laws%5C%22%3EBJP%20Equates%20UCC%20With%20Gender%20Justice.%20But%20Can%20It%20End%20Discrimination%20In-Built%20in%20Personal%20Laws%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20present%20government%20has%20a%20bad%20track%20record%20as%20far%20as%20reforms%20for%20women%E2%80%99s%20equal%20rights%20are%20concerned.%20It%20has%20never%20prioritized%20gender%20justice%20or%20carried%20out%20a%20single%20reform%20for%20women.%C2%A0%20Despite%20several%20demands%20to%20reform%20some%20of%20the%20Hindu%20personal%20laws%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20no%20action%20has%20been%20taken%20by%20the%20Government%20to%20change%20these%20laws%20and%20bring%20equitable%20laws%20for%20these%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20strongly%20feel%20that%20the%20UCC%20is%20merely%20an%20attempt%20to%20undo%20the%20existing%20Muslim%20Law%20and%20laws%20which%20come%20under%20the%20Sixth%20Schedule%2C%20pertaining%20to%20the%20tribal%20areas.%20In%20keeping%20with%20democratic%20norms%2C%20this%20can%20only%20be%20done%20after%20extensive%20discussions%20with%20the%20communities%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20seen%20how%20Muslim%20girls%20have%20been%20targeted%20for%20exercising%20their%20choice%20to%20wear%20a%20Hijab%2C%20and%20how%20this%20has%20affected%20their%20fundamental%20right%20to%20education.%20Also%2C%20the%20Central%20Government%20without%20protecting%20the%20rights%20of%20divorced%20Muslim%20women%2C%20initiated%20the%20law%20to%20put%20Muslim%20men%20in%20jail%20with%20an%20obvious%20communal%20intent%20for%20a%20practice%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20already%20declared%20null%20and%20void.%20Muslim%20youth%20who%20have%20been%20in%20consensual%20relationships%20with%20Hindu%20women%20have%20been%20targeted%20and%20jailed%20in%20several%20fictitious%20cases%20of%20%E2%80%98Love%20Jihad%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20apprehend%20that%20on%20the%20pretext%20of%20re-examining%20the%20need%20for%20a%20UCC%2C%20the%20effort%20will%20largely%20be%20to%20bring%20in%20uniform%20laws%20which%20will%20be%20majoritarian%20laws%2C%20and%20not%20laws%20which%20give%20substantive%20equal%20rights%20to%20women.%20As%20said%20earlier%2C%20uniformity%20of%20law%20by%20itself%20will%20not%20result%20in%20equality%20for%20women%2C%20and%20in%20fact%20will%20probably%20result%20in%20duplicating%20Hindu%20laws%20and%20its%20gender%20biases%20on%20all%20communities%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHindu%20women%20in%20our%20country%20have%20suffered%20because%20they%20do%20not%20have%20equal%20guardianship%20rights%20over%20their%20children.%20They%20also%20do%20not%20have%20equal%20rights%20over%20marital%20property.%20This%20is%20property%20which%20is%20acquired%20by%20either%20party%20during%20the%20subsistence%20of%20a%20marriage%2C%20and%20several%20countries%20recognize%20that%20women%20have%20an%20equal%20share%20in%20this%20property.%20Recently%20a%20Judgement%20of%20the%20Madras%20High%20Court%20recognised%20the%20equal%20value%20of%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20household%20work%20and%20held%20that%20she%20was%20entitled%20to%20an%20equal%20share%20of%20the%20assets%20acquired%20by%20the%20parties%2C%20whether%20she%20had%20financially%20contributed%20towards%20them%20or%20not.%20However%2C%20despite%20several%20women%E2%80%99s%20organizations%20and%20groups%20asking%20for%20this%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20response%20from%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20law%20which%20our%20organization%20and%20others%20have%20been%20demanding%20is%20a%20stand-alone%20and%20comprehensive%20law%20to%20deal%20with%20crimes%20and%20killings%20in%20the%20name%20of%20honour.%20This%20law%20was%20envisaged%20to%20punish%20both%20members%20and%20extended%20members%20of%20the%20family%20as%20well%20as%20community%20panchayats%2C%20who%20torture%20and%20harass%20young%20couples%20and%20deny%20them%20their%20choice%20in%20marriages%20and%20relationships.%20Though%20AIDWA%20gave%20proposals%20for%20such%20a%20law%20in%202005%20and%20also%20to%20the%20present%20Government%2C%20nothing%20has%20been%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Hindu%20and%20other%20women%20do%20not%20have%20equal%20land%20rights%20in%20agricultural%20property%20in%20some%20states%2C%20including%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Uttarakhand.%20Both%20these%20states%20exclude%20married%20daughters%20from%20inheriting%20these%20properties%20on%20specious%20grounds.%20Though%20the%20Hindu%20Succession%20Act%20was%20amended%20in%202005%20to%20remove%20an%20exception%20which%20exempted%20agricultural%20land%20from%20the%20purview%20of%20the%20HSA%2C%20the%20inheritance%20to%20agricultural%20land%20continues%20to%20be%20governed%20by%20some%20state%20laws%20which%20actively%20stop%20women%20from%20this%20inheritance.%20In%20fact%2C%20these%20laws%20have%20been%20placed%20in%20the%20Ninth%20Schedule%20of%20the%20Constitution%20with%20the%20intention%20of%20keeping%20them%20outside%20the%20purview%20of%20courts.%20The%20Hindu%20Succession%20Act%20also%20contains%20an%20unfair%20and%20unjust%20provision%20for%20succession%20to%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20self-acquired%20property%20which%20privileges%20her%20husband%E2%80%99s%20heirs%20over%20her%20own%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20her%20husband%20and%20children.%20However%2C%20this%20has%20also%20not%20been%20amended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20we%20had%20suggested%20that%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20be%20amended%20to%20remove%20the%20one-month%20notice%20and%20waiting%20period%20for%20a%20marriage%20to%20take%20place%20under%20it.%20This%20would%20facilitate%20more%20secular%20marriages%20and%20marriages%20by%20choice.%20It%20is%20well%20known%20that%20the%20one-month%20notice%20period%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20gives%20time%20to%20all%20sorts%20of%20objections%20by%20members%20of%20a%20girl%E2%80%99s%20or%20boy%E2%80%99s%20family%2C%20who%20do%20not%20want%20the%20marriage%20to%20take%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20some%20of%20the%20suggestions%20that%20have%20been%20made%20for%20several%20years%20by%20us%20and%20other%20women%E2%80%99s%20organizations%20to%20bring%20about%20equal%20rights%20for%20women.%20However%2C%20previous%20and%20the%20current%20Government%20have%20consistently%20ignored%20these%20demands.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20some%20State%20governments%20have%20raised%20the%20bogey%20of%20Love%20Jihad%20and%20brought%20about%20draconian%20anti-conversion%20laws%20to%20stop%20inter-faith%20marriages%20by%20choice%20and%20are%20now%20seeking%20to%20bring%20about%20a%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20uniformity%2C%20per%20se.%20There%20is%20also%20talk%20of%20a%20law%20for%20divorce%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20irretrievable%20breakdown%20of%20marriage.%20However%2C%20this%20would%20leave%20most%20women%20without%20any%20means%20of%20survival%20unless%20they%20have%20an%20equal%20right%20to%20marital%20property%20and%20proper%20maintenance%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20a%20rich%20tradition%20of%20both%20plural%20family%20laws%20and%20common%20laws%20in%20areas%20in%20which%20family%20laws%20don%E2%80%99t%20exist.%20As%20stated%20earlier%20the%20Dowry%20Prohibition%20Act%2C%20the%20Commission%20of%20Sati%20(Prevention)%20Act%2C%20the%20Prohibition%20of%20Child%20Marriage%20Act%2C%20the%20Protection%20of%20Women%20from%20Domestic%20Violence%20Act%20are%20common%20laws%20which%20apply%20to%20all%20communities%2C%20as%20can%20a%20law%20on%20the%20crimes%20and%20killings%20in%20the%20name%20of%20%E2%80%98honour%E2%80%99%20and%20a%20law%20on%20equal%20rights%20to%20marital%20property.%20Simultaneously%2C%20reforms%20within%20personal%20laws%20should%20take%20place%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20members%20particularly%20women%20of%20the%20concerned%20community%20and%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20request%20the%20Law%20Commission%20not%20to%20re-examine%20the%20issue%20merely%20because%20the%20Government%20is%20determined%20to%20bring%20about%20a%20UCC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20our%20experience%20in%20the%20field%2C%20we%20would%20also%20like%20to%20give%20oral%20evidence%20to%20the%20Law%20Commission%20when%20it%20calls%20us.%20We%20feel%20that%20women%E2%80%99s%20organizations%20and%20groups%20and%20others%20concerned%20with%20the%20issue%20must%20be%20widely%20consulted%20by%20the%20Law%20Commission%2C%20particularly%20women%20from%20the%20minority%20communities%20and%20Tribal%20women%20before%20it%20decides%20to%20recommend%20a%20UCC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYours%20sincerely%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EP.K.%20Sreemathi%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdv%20Kirti%20Singh%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0Mariam%20Dhawale%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%20President%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegal%20Advisor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%20General%20Secretary%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689221720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F19120045%2F